{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c96205ad-c9eb-424f-9f7d-eab02504c149","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results and display the reason message in the report output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"721f00d1-81fd-4451-9434-c2d4f5027985","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":222,"requestId":"E3C2:1EA0D0:58B94F:65D743:6A052396"},"id":"81fcde96-817b-4b4b-af07-542854cc62d5","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:21:33.498Z","parentId":"856b5f4b-72f7-4512-9b66-0b6eff70910c"}
